author: peters
msg: Followup to r1033665, suggested by stsp.
(revision-install): Guard a $(MKDIR) with a 'test -d' so it does not
run if the directory already exists.  This should not actually be
necessary ($(MKDIR) should be mkdir -p or equivalent), but we've
made the same conservative assumption in the 'mkdir-init' target.
